          <h1>About</h1>
          <p>After over twenty years as Head of Modelmaking and Photography with Richard Rogers, I am uniquely placed to offer model making consultancy for bespoke In-house workshops and recruitment for model makers.</p>

          <p>I have the experience, the skillset and all the contacts to design and deliver quality maker spaces creating everything from fast sketch or concept models to fully detailed competition entries or marketing/exhibition models. I can incorporate flexible photographic areas to create high quality digital images for presentations, documents and exhibition.</p>

          <p>I can guide you through the process, show you how to make it pay and staff it. I have designed workshops from scratch - road tested and adapted each to new technologies and growing teams. I have built a large network of industry connections in London, the UK and internationally and have acquired the knowledge from years of recruitment to source and identify the right modelmakers to place in the best positions.</p>

          <p>I promote making through teaching at BA hons degree and MA levels and devising educational workshops. I have design and Installation experience for exhibitions in London, Europe and the Far East. I have written for the Architects Journal and continue to write columns and books.</p>

          <p>I love creative ideas and projects and am keen to broaden my experience into new areas.</p>
        </article>
